Announcements

Apr 26, 2021

i-Ready just got even better! Here's what's new:

  • Batch print reports for all students at once, without restriction.

  • Share student reports more securely and efficiently when using batch printing.

  • Engage students in fractions with the new Cloud Machine puzzle creator.

  • New Middle School Reading Comprehension lessons are now available.

  • New Spanish Math lessons for Grades 2–3 are now available.

  • New Spanish Phonics lessons for Grades K–2 are now available.

  • Ongoing accessibility improvements in Personalized Instruction are now available.

To learn more, please visit our What's New page.

Mar 7, 2021

i-Ready just got even better! Here's what's new:

  • The For Families report now includes new language to support conversations with families.

  • You will now be able to access, share, and embed links to individual Online Educator Learning courses.

  • We added keyboard navigation to most Reading Comprehension lessons for Grades 6-8.

Feb 1, 2021

Show/Hide Assessments for a Student

Student Roster settings are now simpler and allow you to show or hide an assessment for specific students when proctoring the Diagnostic.

Dec 17, 2020

Our winter release is here! Here's what's new:

  • Administrators can enable teachers to use Standards Mastery as a classroom formative assessment.

  • We expanded our tools to address unfinished learning in Math and Reading.

  • Closed Captioning is available in most Personalized Instruction lessons.

  • The For Families report shows more data to support conversations with families.

  • New Spanish lessons are available for Grade 1 in Math and Reading.

  • All K–2 Phonics lessons are responsive and let students move on when they show they know a skill.

  • Student settings are simpler for you to use.

Discover even more improvements and see details at What's New for 20-21.

Nov 10, 2020

Updates to Oral Reading Fluency Assessments Materials

The Oral Reading Fluency Assessments Administration Manual and Retell Rubric were updated on October 12, 2020. Minor changes to the Manual clarify how various scores are used to gauge oral reading fluency performance and progress. Changes to the Retell Rubric influence whether a student is scored as proficient or below in comprehension as part of the Oral Reading Fluency Assessments. Please download and use the most recent Manual and Retell Rubric to administer Oral Reading Fluency Assessments moving forward. For additional resources and tools, visit i-ReadyCentral.com/ReadingFluency.

Oct 11, 2020

i-Ready just got even better. Here's what's new:

  • The Prerequisites report now covers additional Math topics and skills.

  • Tools for Scaffolding Comprehension have been expanded, covering skills related to key ideas and details, as well as craft and structure.

  • Middle School Math concepts are now included in the Learning Game Match.

  • Our coverage of authentic Spanish Phonics skills for Grade K is complete with the release of new Reading lessons.

  • Demographic data filters were added to the district and school Personalized Instruction Summary report. Available for districts and schools that share demographic data with i-Ready.

  • Can Do's and Next Steps for each domain can be accessed from the top of the student Diagnostic Results report.

  • Hide Assessment Access is more clearly labeled and simpler to use.

  • Filter by language on the district and school Diagnostic Results report. Available for administrators in schools or districts using the Diagnostic for Mathematics in Spanish.

Click here for more details and to discover everything that's new this school year.

Sep 4, 2020

i-Ready just got even better with tools to support you in the new school year. It's now simpler to:

  • Control when students take the Diagnostic with the Hide Assessment Access feature, now available for leaders.

  • Save time when assigning lessons with the ability to assign i-Ready lessons to all students in a grade at once, across a school or district.

  • Strategically prepare students for grade-level learning with the Prerequisites report for Mathematics and Tools for Scaffolding Comprehension for Reading.

  • Get more detailed student placement information with a five-level view of Diagnostic Results.

  • Better understand students' progress last year with historical lesson data in the Personalized Instruction by Lesson report.

  • Help students build key skills with newly released lessons, including more authentic Spanish Phonics for Grade K, Expressions and Equations for Grades 6–7, and Fractions for Grades 3–4.

For more details, see our Back to School release notes and new feature walkthrough video.

Aug 21, 2020

New Feature: Hide Assessment Access

Hide Assessment Access is available now for teachers. Use this new feature to control when students take the Diagnostic by manually turning assessments on and off for a class or a report group. This feature may be helpful if your district or school assessment plan calls for virtually proctoring the Diagnostic or for ensuring students take the Diagnostic on days when they are at school, if your buildings remain open. Click here to learn more.

Jul 19, 2020

Our annual back to school release is here, and it's packed with updates that will make i-Ready more motivating and accessible for students, and more powerful and flexible for educators. Here's what's new:

  • Ability to see all teacher-assigned lessons at a glance.

  • Teacher Toolbox integrated into i-Ready.

  • New online learning platform that digitally extends professional development.

  • More powerful ways to analyze data, with new exports and demographic data filters added to more reports.

  • Motivating new instruction for Middle Schoolers, with access to learning games.

  • Engaging, shorter lessons for elementary learners in Phonics and fractions.

  • Ongoing accessibility improvements.

  • And much more!

Click here to see all the improvements coming to i-Ready.

May 3, 2020

Our latest i-Ready release helps you better support your students through remote learning. Here's what's new:

Quickly See How Your Class is Performing. An Early Access version of the new Personalized Instruction by Lesson report for classes and report groups allows you to view performance on recently completed lessons and check the status of in progress lessons. Using this report, you can now:

  • Check student performance on lessons they've completed in the prior two weeks and see the status of Teacher-Assigned Lessons that are available to students.
  • Identify students who are working in similar levels and domains for grouping.
  • See which lessons students are struggling with, before there's an alert.

The functionality of this report will be expanded for the coming school year.

Keep Student Queues Tidy. To keep Teacher-Assigned Lesson queues manageable, i-Ready Teacher-Assigned Lessons will now be removed from a student's queue 60 days after their due date.

Engage Middle Schoolers' Critical Thinking. Introducing a new type of middle school Reading Comprehension lesson that focuses on connecting ideas in complex passages.

Mar 15, 2020

i-Ready just got even better to support your teaching and learning. Here's what's new:

  • Turn My Stuff on or off for the entire class from the Rosters page.

  • The class Standards Performance report is simpler and now shows a dash if students are not able to get a green check for a standard.

  • Teachers now pick an "available date" when assigning lessons so students aren't overwhelmed with too many tasks at a time.

  • A small number of Math lessons in Spanish for Kindergarten are available as Early Access and can be assigned by teachers.

Dec 15, 2019

Our winter release is here, and it's packed with many of the improvements most requested by educators. Here's what's new:

  • Print the student Diagnostic Results on a single page.

  • Download data directly from most reports, with your sorting and filtering preserved.

  • See the average percent of online lessons that students passed last week.

  • Work in i-Ready for a full hour without needing to sign in again.

  • Turn Learning Games on or off for the entire class.

  • See growth data from last year in the district and school Diagnostic Growth reports.

  • Use Spanish versions of Tools for Instruction for math.

  • And so much more!

Click here to see a complete list of all the improvements available today!

Nov 26, 2019

Update for Users of Export Files

With improvements coming this winter, accessing and analyzing your i-Ready data will be simpler and more powerful.

We will be making changes to export files as part of these improvements. These changes might impact analysis you conduct with exports.

If you use your data outside of i-Ready, please read our documentation to determine if you need to change how you use exports.

Nov 10, 2019

i-Ready just got even better with motivating new instruction for your students. Here's what's new:

  • New Math lessons for Grades 1–4 that offer a brand new approach to Word Problems.

  • New Middle School Math lessons for Grades 6–8 focused on percent and rational numbers.

  • Improvements to Phonics lessons for Grades K–2 that make the instruction shorter and even more age appropriate.

  • New Tools for Instruction focused on Financial Literacy skills.

Aug 18, 2019

i-Ready just got even better. Here's what's new:

  • The To Do page on the student dashboard is accessible to students with visual, auditory, and physical impairments.

  • Teachers can gauge the progress of a student towards reaching a Mid On Grade Level placement, which indicates a student has achieved the expectations of their grade-level standards at the end of the school year. The scale score needed to reach this placement level is now clearly shown in the student reports for Diagnostic Results and Diagnostic Growth.

  • Download what you see on screen by selecting new CSV download buttons on the school- and district-level reports for Diagnostic Results and Online Instruction.

  • Column headers in your reports are sticky, so you always know what data you're viewing as you scroll down a report.

  • Scale scores are shown in Instructional Groupings, so you don't need to click into a separate report to see them.

  • See all schools and grade levels across your district in a single view in the Diagnostic Results and Online Instruction reports for district administrators.

  • Know which teachers have assigned i-Ready lessons by viewing a new Assigned by column on the Manage Schedule page for Online Instruction.

  • Canceling teacher-assigned lessons is simpler with the new Cancel by Student functionality, which is also found in the Manage Schedule page for Online Instruction.

Jul 21, 2019

Our annual back to school release is here, and it is packed with updates that will make i-Ready more motivating and accessible for students, and more powerful for educators. Here's what's new:

  • A new grade-banded student dashboard, with new ways to see progress.

  • New online lessons for both Middle Schoolers and elementary grades.

  • New Learning Games in Mathematics for K–5 students.

  • Major accessibility improvements for the Diagnostic.

  • Many enhancements for educators, including new historical reporting of Diagnostic data.

  • And much more!

Watch our preview video and click here to see a complete list of our improvements for back to school 2019.

Feb 24, 2019

i-Ready just got even better. Here's what's new:

  • New Online Instruction report at the district- and school-levels. Use this new real-time report to monitor instructional usage, the percent of lessons passed, and the number of students across a district or school with instructional alerts who may need additional support. With this report, administrators can track the same key metrics available to teachers in student- and class-level reports.

    • Note: PDF versions of the Instructional Usage report will remain available for this school year via the View Legacy Reports link.

  • Click into grade levels in your reports. Administrators can now click into grade-level data from most district- and school-level reports, providing a simpler way to analyze your data.

  • Standards Mastery data available in real-time on the Teacher Dashboard. Teachers now have a quick view on their dashboard into how students performed on their most recent Standards Mastery test.

  • New Tools for Instruction in Vocabulary. Twenty-six brand new Tools for Instruction in Vocabulary are now available across Grades K–8.

  • New Game on Student Dashboard. Students who have earned credits from completing lessons will be able to play our new game, BeGooped.

Dec 16, 2018

i-Ready Learning Games are Here!

These six engaging i-Ready Learning Games are available for students in Grades K-4. The games:

  • Offer practice in fluency and challenging elementary mathematics standards.

  • Foster internal motivation through engaging challenges.

  • Give every student a personalized experience based on data from the i-Ready Diagnostic.

You can demo our games by going to your Learning Games homescreen or visit i-ReadyCentral.com/LearningGames to review our resources.

Dec 16, 2018

i-Ready just got even better. Here's what's new:

  • New Diagnostic reports for district and school leaders. Three new reports provide actionable, real-time insight into student performance.

    • Diagnostic Results gives a clear view of your progress towards proficiency and annual growth expectations and enables you to easily compare the results of two Diagnostics side by side. (Replaces the Performance by Grade and Class, Needs Analysis by Grade, and Intervention Screener reports.)

    • Diagnostic Status shows you the real-time progress of a Diagnostic as it is being administered and lets you see if students have rush flags or are at risk of having their tests expire. (Replaces the Diagnostic Completion Export.)

    • Instructional Groupings groups students who share similar instructional needs across a grade within a school, and for each group, provides detailed instructional priorities and classroom resources to support differentiated instruction. (Replaces the Instructional Groupings Profile.)

  • Legacy reports remain available for this school year. A new link in your reports navigation gives you access to the PDF version of district- and school-level reports that have been replaced.

  • New Vocabulary lessons for students placing in Grades 3–5. We released 44 cutting-edge online lessons that are designed to help students build word learning strategies.

  • i-Ready is 100% out of Adobe Flash and fully available to students on supported iPads. i-Ready is now all-HTML5, including all assessments and every online lesson.

Oct 14, 2018

i-Ready just got even better. Here's what's new:

  • New Diagnostic Growth reports show growth between Diagnostics and progress towards annual growth measures.

  • The redesigned Growth Monitoring Results report is now available.

  • New Math practice lessons are available for students working in Grades 4 and 5 online instruction.

  • Searching for a student across schools is now available to district administrators and any school administrator with access to multiple schools.

  • A student's grade level is now visible on the header of all student-level reports.

  • Duplicate a report group or a class using the Add Report Group or Add Class actions.

  • The new Standards Mastery Status report lets you track the progress of any tests that have been assigned and are not yet completed for a class.

  • Cancel a Standards Mastery assignment for a student without needing to know the class a student is enrolled in.

Aug 26, 2018

i-Ready just got even better. We've released several updates to make i-Ready simpler and more actionable for you.

  • Print reports for multiple students using batch reports.

  • See your state standards in a student's Diagnostic Results report.

  • Cancel all teacher-assigned lessons for one or more students in a single action.

  • Use a teacher's name to search for a class in your reports.

  • See all students associated with a teacher in your class reports.

  • Turn Online Instruction on or off by class or report group on the Rosters page.

  • See Assessment Access Restrictions on your Assessment page and revert to district settings with a click.

  • Use the Growth Monitoring Status report to ensure students complete Growth Checks.

  • Export passwords using the Actions menu on the Rosters page. (Applies if your district uses i-Ready login credentials to sign in.)

  • Change your own password using My Profile. (Applies if your district uses i-Ready login credentials to sign in.)
